      "side": 1,
      "message": "So I\u0027m missing how the profiles/Meters are assigned to whatever -\u003e some flow? To which flow? And what is the real effect of the setting on both the OLT and ONU. Is their effect always only related to upstream (currently on the ONU yes, on the OLT?)? Is the same profile applied with the same value to both OLT and the ONU? This generally does not fit together - a service may be related to multiple GemPorts (defined by the attached TechProfile). So basically the idea might have been to police/rate limit the upstream traffic on the ONU already according to the T-Cont bandwidth allocation ensured by the OLT (in my point of view makes only sense for a T-Cont type with some BestEffort bandwidth). But practically this currently only works for an attached TechProfile with just 1 GemPort. As the values are applied to all (existing) GemPorts (that may be related to the service) for the ONU, the resulting bandwidth in the T-Cont for the ONU is much higher than what expect the OLT T-CONT really enforces.",
